A former aide to President Muhammadu Buhari, Bashir Ahmad has sparked mixed reactions among social media users after he shared a photo of the All Progressive Congress (APC) vice presidential candidate, Kashim Shettima with the United States president, Joe Biden.
Taking to his official Twitter page a few moments ago, he shared a photo of Kashim Shettima shaking the United States President, Joe Biden. Sharing the photo, he wrote, “The US President and incoming VP, KSM”.
Take a look at the photo along with the caption he shared:
Immediately after he made this post on his Twitter page, it generated a lot of controversies online as a lot of social media users stormed to the comments section of the post to air their opinions/thoughts about his tweet.
@adahobehira: “Incoming you said, it’s going to be tough no one is incoming”
@naijaforPO: “Continue dreaming ooo”
